com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models

Class ListQueuesResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models.ListQueuesResult

  • public class ListQueuesResult
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class for the results returned in response to Queue service REST API operations to list queues. This is returned by calls to implementations of QueueContract.listQueues() and QueueContract.listQueues(ListQueuesOptions).

    See the List Queues documentation on MSDN for details of the underlying Queue service REST API operation.

      • getAccountName

        public java.lang.String getAccountName()
        Gets the base URI for Queue service REST API operations on the storage account. The URI consists of the protocol along with the DNS prefix name for the account followed by ".queue.core.windows.net". For example, if the DNS prefix name for the storage account is "myaccount" then the value returned by this method is "http://myaccount.queue.core.windows.net".
        Returns:
        A String containing the base URI for Queue service REST API operations on the storage account.

      • getPrefix

        public java.lang.String getPrefix()
        Gets the prefix String used to qualify the results returned by the listQueues request. Only queues with names that start with the prefix are returned by the request. By default, the prefix is empty and all queues are returned.
        Returns:
        The String prefix used to qualify the names of the queues returned.

      • getMarker

        public java.lang.String getMarker()
        Gets the marker value for the beginning of the queue results returned by the listQueues request. The marker is used by the server to specify the place to resume a query for queues. The marker value is a String opaque to the client. A listQueues request response may include a NextMarker value if there are more queue results than can be returned in a single response. Call the getNextMarker method to get this value. The client can request the next set of queue results by setting the marker to this value in the ListQueuesOptions parameter. By default, this value is empty and the server responds with the first queues that match the request.
        Returns:
        A String containing the marker value used for the response.

      • setMarker

        public void setMarker(java.lang.String marker)
        Reserved for internal use. Sets the marker value specifying the beginning of the results returned by the Queue service REST API list queues operation invoked with a call to listQueues. This method is invoked by the API as part of the response generation from the Queue service REST API operation to set the value from the Marker element returned by the server.
        Parameters:
        marker - A String containing the marker value used for the response.

      • getNextMarker

        public java.lang.String getNextMarker()
        Gets the next marker value needed to retrieve additional queues. If more queues are available that satisfy a listQueues request than can be returned in the response, the server generates a marker value to specify the beginning of the queues to return in a subsequent request. The client can request the next set of queue results by setting the marker to this value in the ListQueuesOptions parameter. This value is empty if there are no more queues that satisfy the request than are included in the response.
        Returns:
        A String containing the marker value to use to resume the list queues request.

      • setNextMarker

        public void setNextMarker(java.lang.String nextMarker)

Sets the next marker value specifying the place to resume a list queues query if more results are available than have been returned by the Queue service REST API list queues operation response. This method is invoked by the API as part of the response generation from the Queue service REST API operation to set the value from the NextMarker element returned by the server.
        Parameters:
        nextMarker - A String containing the marker value to use to resume the list queues request.

      • getMaxResults

        public int getMaxResults()
        Gets the value specified for the number of queue results to return for the listQueues request. The server will not return more than this number of queues in the response. If the value is not specified, the server will return up to 5,000 items.

        If there are more queues available that match the request than the number returned, the response will include a next marker value to specify the beginning of the queues to return in a subsequent request. Call the getNextMarker method to get this value. The client can request the next set of queue results by setting the marker to this value in the ListQueuesOptions parameter.

        Returns:
        The maximum number of results to return specified by the request.

      • setMaxResults

This method is invoked by the API as part of the response generation from the Queue service REST API operation to set the value from the MaxResults element returned by the server.
        Parameters:
        maxResults - The maximum number of results to return specified by the request.
